which you may redistribute a given source file.  Most of the source
code contributed to Jmol has nearly identical distribution
restrictions to those that are imposed below.

Jmol now includes jar files for 2 additional packages that aid in
parsing CML files:

    AElfred, is a Java-based XML parser from Microstar.  It is free
             for both commercial and non-commercial use, and COMES
             WITH NO WARRANTY.  Details on and source code for AElfred
             are available at:  http://www.microstar.com/aelfred.html

        SAX, is a free API for event-based XML parsing.  It is free
             for both commercial and non-commercial use.  Details on
             and source code for SAX are available at:
             http://www.megginson.com/SAX/

Jmol also includes jar files for the Acme Image encoders by Jef Poskanzer
(http://www.acme.com) as well as the junit Java testing framework 
(http://www.xprogramming.com/software.htm)

The Ptolemy PtPlot Library (http://ptolemy.eecs.berkeley.edu/) is used for viewing plots. 
Copyright (C) 1997-1999 The Regents of the University of California. 
All rights reserved. 

